===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
[[oracle bone script|Oracle bone script]]: {{Han compound|宀|琡|貝|ls=ic|t1=house|t2=jade|t3=cowry}} – treasures in a house.

The phonetic component {{och-l|缶}} was added to the character in bronze inscriptions.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*pəw||price}}; cognate with {{cog|my|အဖိုး||price}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; STEDT). {{zh-ref|Peiros and Starostin (1996)}} also compares it to {{cog|bo|སྤུས|t=goods}}. {{zh-ref|Sagart (1999)}} relates it to {{och-l|富|rich}}. {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} proposes that it could be the same word as {{och-l|保|to take care of; to consider something precious}}.

